      {
        "q": "Does Dr. Sara accept new patients?",
        "a": "Yes, Dr. Sara is currently accepting new patients. You can book your first appointment directly through the platform."
      },
      {
        "q": "What insurance plans are accepted?",
        "a": "Dr. Sara accepts most major insurance plans including Allianz, AXA, MetLife, and Cairo Amman Bank health insurance. Please verify with the clinic before your visit."
      },
      {
        "q": "Is telemedicine available for first visits?",
        "a": "Telemedicine is available for follow-up visits and consultations that do not require a physical examination. First visits for new conditions typically require an in-person appointment."
      },
      {
        "q": "How long are appointments typically?",
        "a": "A standard consultation lasts approximately 20–30 minutes. Comprehensive cardiac evaluations may take up to 60 minutes."
      },
      {
        "q": "Can I get a prescription online?",
        "a": "Yes, for established patients with existing conditions, Dr. Sara can issue prescription renewals through the telemedicine platform."
      },
      {
        "q": "What languages does the doctor speak?",
        "a": "Dr. Sara speaks both Arabic and English fluently and conducts consultations in either language based on patient preference."
      }
    ],
